Name: TELREADOUT
Description: A single scaler accumulation interval, and the first and last records and SCLKs for which the interval was in effect.

Name: grand_start_sclk
Description: The first SCLK for which this readout is applicable

Name: grand_stop_sclk
Description: The last SCLK for which this readout is applicable

Name: grand_interval
Description: The duration of the interval.

Name: comment
Description: Remarks about the containing object.

Name: TELREADOUT_List
Description: A list of scaler accumulation intervals, along with the records for which they were in effect.

Name: TELSOH
Description: A single state-of-health accumulation interval, and the first and last records and SCLKs for which the interval was in effect.

Name: grand_start_sclk
Description: The first SCLK for which this readout is applicable

Name: grand_stop_sclk
Description: The last SCLK for which this readout is applicable

Name: grand_interval
Description: The duration of the interval.

Name: comment
Description: Remarks about the containing object.

Name: TELSOH_List
Description: A list of state-of-health accumulation intervals, along with the records for which they were in effect.

Name: FC
Description: The Dawn FC" class is the container for Dawn Framing Camera (FC) specific metadata elements. "

Name: callamp_delay_time
Description: Callamp switch on delay measured in microseconds after START_TIME. Callamp can be switched on before (less than 193000 µs), at (= 193000 µs), or after (greater than 193000 µs) begin of exposure.

Name: callamp_duty
Description: The callamp can be run at various duty cycles between 0.0 % and 100.0 % by using only every other pulse of the callamp frequency to trigger the callamp. DAWN_CALLAMP_DUTY = CALLAMP_FREQUENCY / Value * 100 % Example: Value = 1.0 : DAWN_CALLAMP_DUTY = 100 % Value = 2.5 : DAWN_CALLAMP_DUTY = 40 % This calculation is done internally in the camera, the user commands the requensted duty cycle in percentage.

Name: callamp_enable_flag
Description: Indicates if callamp is enabled or disabled during image acquisition.

Name: OFF
Description: callamp set to disabled

Name: ON
Description: callamp set to enabled

Name: callamp_frequency
Description: The callamp frequency is determined by the internal 24 MHz clock and an integer divisor. CALLAMP_FREQUENCY = 24 MHz / Value The standard callamp frequency is 100 kHz (24MHz / 240).

Name: callamp_strobe_time
Description: Callamp strobe time is measured in microseconds after callamp switch on. callamp switch off time = START_TIME + DAWN_CALLAMP_DELAY_TIME + DAWN_CALLAMP_STROBE_TIME

Name: chamber
Description: This keyword was used during ground tests to describe the test environment.

Name: data_routing_id
Description: This keyword describes the priority of the acquired image and thus how it was handled on board.

Name: Op-Nav
Description: The image is processed with highest priority and streamed into VR10 of the s/c.

Name: Science 1
Description: The image is processed with high priority and streamed into VR8 of the s/c.

Name: Science 2
Description: The image is processed with mid priority and streamed into VR8 of the s/c.

Name: Science 3
Description: The image is processed with low priority and streamed into VR8 of the s/c.

Name: Science 4
Description: The image is processed with least priority and streamed into VR8 of the s/c.

Name: dpu_hardware_id
Description: Both DPUs for FC1 and FC2 have the same DPU ID because they are identical.

Name: dpu_software_version
Description: Current version of the FC onboard software

Name: fee_flag
Description: OFF = FEE is disabled, images cannot be acquired ON = FEE is enabled, images can be acquired

Name: OFF
Description: FEE is disabled, images cannot be acquired

Name: ON
Description: FEE is enabled, images can be acquired

Name: fee_hardware_id
Description: The fee_hardware_id attribute indicates the identifer associated with each Framing Camera.
FEE ID of FC2 (FM2)
FEE ID of FC1 (FS1)
indicates that the FEE is off or busy and cannot transmit its ID.

Name: filter_encoder
Description: FILTER_NUMBER = (((64 + 4 + encoderOnClearFilter - FILTER_ENCODER) / 8) MOD 8) + 1 encoderOnClearFilter is a hardware-dependent constant filterEncoder is the current readout of the encoder filterNumber return a value in the range [1..8]. All the operation are integer operations, MOD represents modulo and / is the integer division. The subtraction is negative (F1 - Fx) because the encoder value decreases with increasing filter number.

Name: front_door_status_id
Description: The front_door_status_id attribute indicates the status of the Front Door, covering the camera aperture, when the image was acquired. In the case of windowed images, this value is the same for all the subframes.

Name: CLOSED
Description: Front Door is closed.

Name: OPEN
Description: Front Door is open.

Name: front_door_encoder
Description: The Front Door is closed if FRONT_DOOR_ENCODER shows the nominal value +/- 1 and otherwise is open.

Name: fsa_shoot_enable_flag
Description: The fsa_shoot_enable_flag attribute determines if the Fail Safe Actuator is enabled. For saftey safety reasons, the FSA requires two switches to be active at the same time in order to be active. One of them alone will have no effect.

Name: OFF
Description: The Fail Safe Actuator for the Front Door is disabled.

Name: ON
Description: The Fail Safe Actuator for the Front Door is enabled. FSA_SHOOT_FLAG can be switched ON now.

Name: fsa_shoot_flag
Description: The fsa_shoot_flag attribute determines if the Fail-Safe Actuator is active.

Name: OFF
Description: The Fail Safe Actuator for the Front Door is switched off.

Name: ON
Description: The Fail Safe Actuator for the Front Door is switched on.

Name: heater0_flag
Description: The heater0_flag attribute indicates status of the Camera Head Heater. The heater produces 4.4 W (5.6 Ohm at +5 V).

Name: OFF
Description: The CH heater (HEATER0) is switched on.

Name: ON
Description: The CH heater (HEATER0) is switched off.

Name: heater1_flag
Description: The heater1_flag attribute indicates the status of the Baffle Heater. The heater produces 1.0 W (26 Ohm at +5 V)

Name: OFF
Description: The Baffle heater (HEATER1) is switched on.

Name: ON
Description: The Baffle heater (HEATER1) is switched off.

Name: image_acquire_mode
Description: The image_acquire_mode attribute indicates the FC mode setting of image acquisition.

Name: DARK
Description: The image was acquired with Front Door closed and the Callamp off.

Name: FLATFIELD
Description: The image was acquired with Front Door closed and the Callamp on.

Name: NORMAL
Description: The image was acquired with Front Door open.

Name: SERIAL
Description: The artificial image shows the readout of the serial register.

Name: STORAGE
Description: The image shows the readout of the storage area of the CCD.

Name: TEST_CH
Description: The artificial iamge shows a test pattern with DNs from 0 to 16382.

Name: mcu_flag
Description: The mcu_flag attribute indicates whether the Mechanism Controller Unit (MCU) is powered. It is independent of the MCU motor power flag.

Name: OFF
Description: MCU is disabled, mechanisms cannot be moved.

Name: ON
Description: MCU is enabled, mechanisms (filter wheel and front door) can be moved

Name: mcu_hardware_id
Description: The mcu_hardware_id attribute is an identifier indicating which FC unit is in use.
MCU ID of FC1 (FS1)
MCU ID of FC2 (FM2)

Name: mcu_motor_flag
Description: The mcu_motor_flag indicates if the motors for the mechanisms are powered. This switch and flag are independent of the MCU power flag.

Name: OFF
Description: Both motors (Front Door and Filter wheel) are unpowered.

Name: ON
Description: Both motors are powered. Either to hold their position or to move to another position.

Name: operator
Description: This keyword was used during ground tests to indicate the responsible operator of the test.

Name: pcu_hardware_id
Description: The pcu_hardware_id is an analog value showing the hardware ID of the Power Converter Unit (PCU). The actual value can jitter around the nominal.
PCU ID of FC2 (FM2)
PCU ID of FC1 (FS1)

Name: purpose
Description: This keyword was used during ground tests to describe the purpose of the test.

Name: subject
Description: This keyword was used during ground tests to describe the subject used during the test.

Name: target
Description: This keyword was used during ground tests to describe the target the FC was pointing at during the test

Name: test_lamp
Description: This keyword was used during ground tests to define the lamp that was used during the test.

Name: udplib_software_version
Description: Current version of the FC UDP library

Name: use_pre_clear
Description: The use_pre_clear attribute indicates whether a pre-clear of the CCD was performed prior to image acquisition. A pre-clear is performed 193 ms prior to image acquisition and removes all charge that is on the CCD at the time of execution.

Name: OFF
Description: No pre-clear of the CCD prior to an image acquisition.

Name: ON
Description: A pre-clear of the CCD was performed prior to image acquisition.

Name: alt_start_time
Description: The same time as the start_date_time attribute expressed year/day-of-year rather than year/month/day.

Name: alt_stop_time
Description: The same time as the stop_date_time attribute expressed year/day-of-year rather than year/month/day.

Name: VIR_Operational_Parameters
Description: The VIR_Operational_Parameters contains attributes related to VIR operating mode information, data quality and other similar metadata.

Name: data_quality_id
Description: The data_quality_id is an indicator of whether data files is complete or if there are missing lines.
The data qube is incomplete (there are missing lines).
The data qube is complete.

Name: telemetry_source_id
Description: The telemetry_source_id attribute identifies the Electrical Ground Supporting Equipment (EGSE) used to produce the data file. This attribute is always set to "EGSE".

Name: channel_id
Description: The channel_id identifies the instrument channel producing the data.

Name: IR
Description: The data were produced by the Infrared (IR) channel.

Name: VIS
Description: The data were produced by the Visibile (VIS) channel.

Name: software_version_id
Description: The software_version_id attribute identifies the software used to write the labels and format the data.

Name: instrument_mode_id
Description: The instrument_mode_id attribute identifies the mode that the instrument was in when the data were taken.

Description: Calibration, low spectral high spatial, Quarter slit

Name: C_L_SPE_L_SPA_F
Description: Calibration, low spectral low spatial, Full slit

Description: Science, high spectral high spatial, Full slit

Description: Science, high spectral low spatial, Full slit

Description: Science, high spectral low spatial, Summing

Description: Science, Low spectral high spatial, Full slit

Description: Science, Low spectral low spatial, Full slit

Name: S_L_SPE_L_SPA_F_MEA
Description: Science, low spectral low spatial, Meaning

Name: S_L_SPE_L_SPA_F_SUM
Description: Science, Low spectral low spatial, Summing

Name: scan_mode_id
Description: The scan_mode_id is an integer in the range 0 to 10 that identifies the VIR Scan Mirror mode. "0" means that the mirror was not used. The VIR scan mirror performs, when commanded, and angular movement around an axis parallel to the slit direction (y direction). There can be 10 different modes, each one identifying a given angular movement.

Name: comment
Description: The comment attribute is a character string expressing one or more remarks or thoughts relevant to the object.

Name: Scan_Parameters
Description: The Scan_Parameters class contains attributes describing the activity of the VIR scan mirror.

Name: scan_start_angle
Description: The scan_start_angle attribute indicates the start position of the VIR scan mirror.

Name: scan_stop_angle
Description: The scan_stop_angle attribute indicates the stop position of the VIR scan mirror.

Name: scan_step_angle
Description: The scan_step_angle attribute indicates the size of each step of the VIR scan mirror.

Name: scan_step_number
Description: The scan_step_number attribute indicates the number of acquisitions performed within a single VIR scan mirror unit position.

Name: Frame_Parameters
Description: The Frame_Parameters class contains attributes describing the acquisition of the VIR frames.

Name: exposure_duration
Description: The exposure_duration attribute is the integration time expressed in milliseconds. It is the exposure time of elementary exposures when summing is performed.

Name: frame_summing
Description: The frame_summing attribute is the number of elementary exposures when summing is performed.

Name: external_repetition_time
Description: The external_repetition_time attribute is the time required for a frame acqusition cycle (> exposure_duration * frame_summing).

Name: dark_acquisition_rate
Description: The dar_acquisition_rate attribute is the number of frames acquired between two background measurements.

Name: VIR_Instrument_Temperatures
Description: The VIR_Instrument_Temperatures class contains attributes which identify the temperature in different sections of the VIR instrument.

Name: vir_focal_plane_maximum_temperature
Description: The vir_focal_plane_maximum_temperature indicates the maxiumum temperature on the VIR focal plane during the VIR image acquisition.

Name: vir_telescope_maximum_temperature
Description: The vir_telescope_maximum_temperature indicates the maxiumum temperature on the VIR optical telescope during the VIR image acquisition.

Name: vir_spectrometer_maximum_temperature
Description: The vir_spectrometer_maximum_temperature indicates the maxiumum temperature on the VIR grating spectrometer during the VIR image acquisition.

Name: vir_cryocooler_maximum_temperature
Description: The vir_cyrocooler_maximum_temperature indicates the maxiumum temperature on the VIR cryocooler during the VIR image acquisition.

Name: VIR
Description: The Dawn VIR" class is the container for Dawn Visual and Infrared Spectrometer (VIR) specific metadata elements. "

Name: vir_ir_start_x_position
Description: This keyword gives the X coordinate of the first CCD pixel used on the IR FPA. This quantity determines the correspondence between wavelength and spectral channels.

Name: vir_ir_start_y_position
Description: This keyword gives the Y coordinate of the first CCD pixel used on the IR FPA. This quantity determines the correspondence between wavelength and spectral channels.

Name: vir_vis_start_x_position
Description: This keyword gives the X coordinate of the first CCD pixel used on the VIS FPA. This quantity determines the correspondence between wavelength and spectral channels.

Name: vir_vis_start_y_position
Description: This keyword gives the Y coordinate of the first CCD pixel used on the VIS FPA. This quantity determines the correspondence between wavelength and spectral channels.

Name: GRaND

spacecraft_clock_start_count
Description: The spacecraft_clock_start_count attribute provides the value of the spacecraft clock at the beginning of a time period of interest.

Name: spacecraft_clock_stop_count
Description: The spacecraft_clock_stop_count attribute provides the value of the spacecraft clock at the beginning of a time period of interest.

Name: standard_data_product_id
Description: The standard_data_product_id keyword is used to identify data products of the same processing level that are not otherwise indentified by being in different collections within the bundle.
